.TH UTILITYKIT 1 "July 2026" "UtilityKit v5.10.6" "UtilityKit Tools"
.SH NAME
utility-cheat_sheet \- A personal markdown snippet store. Save, tag, list, display, and search short command references or notes directly from the terminal.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B utility cheat_sheet
[\fIoptions\fP]
.SH DESCRIPTION
A personal markdown snippet store. Save, tag, list, display, and search short command references or notes directly from the terminal.
.SH FEATURES
.PP
.IP \(bu 4
\fBAdd snippets\fP — save any text as a named markdown file with optional tags
.IP \(bu 4
\fBList snippets\fP — show all saved snippet names at a glance
.IP \(bu 4
\fBShow snippets\fP — display the full contents of any saved snippet
.IP \(bu 4
\fBSearch snippets\fP — grep across all saved snippet content and names
.IP \(bu 4
\fBFile input\fP — import an existing file as a snippet instead of typing inline
.IP \(bu 4
\fBInteractive mode\fP — running without arguments launches a persistent menu loop
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH USAGE
.PP
.EX
bash _cheat_sheet/_cheat_sheet.sh --add docker-logs --text 'docker logs -f app' --tags docker,logs

bash _cheat_sheet/_cheat_sheet.sh --add my-nginx-conf --file ./nginx.conf --tags nginx,config

bash _cheat_sheet/_cheat_sheet.sh --list

bash _cheat_sheet/_cheat_sheet.sh --show docker-logs

bash _cheat_sheet/_cheat_sheet.sh --search docker

bash _cheat_sheet/_cheat_sheet.sh
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH OPTIONS
.PP
Option   |   Description
\fC--add NAME\fP   |   Save a new snippet with the given name
\fC--text TEXT\fP   |   Snippet content as an inline string
\fC--file FILE\fP   |   Import content from an existing file
\fC--tags a,b\fP   |   Comma-separated tags stored in the snippet header
\fC--list\fP   |   List all saved snippet names
\fC--show NAME\fP   |   Display the full contents of a named snippet
\fC--search TERM\fP   |   Search all snippets for a term
\fC-h, --help\fP   |   Show usage
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH STORAGE LOCATION
.PP
Snippets are saved as individual markdown files under:
.PP
.EX
~/.local/share/utilitykit/cheat_sheets/
.EE
.PP
Each file is named using a slugified version of the snippet name. Tags are stored in an HTML comment header at the top of each file:
.PP
.EX
<!-- tags: docker,logs -->

docker logs -f app
.EE
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH INTERACTIVE MENU
.PP
Running the tool without arguments opens a persistent loop with four actions:
.PP
.EX
  1) List saved snippets     (show all snippet names you have stored)
  2) Add a new snippet       (save a one-liner or short block with tags)
  3) Show a snippet          (display full contents of a saved snippet)
  4) Search snippets         (grep across all saved snippet content)
  q) Return to dashboard
.EE
.PP
The loop stays open after each action until you press \fCq\fP, so you can list, show, and search without relaunching the tool each time.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH MULTI-LINE SNIPPETS
.PP
When adding a snippet interactively and you leave the text prompt blank, the tool drops into free-form input mode — type as many lines as you need, then press \fCCtrl+D\fP to save.
.PP
.PP
.PP
.SH EXIT CODES
.PP
Code   |   Meaning
\fC0\fP   |   Success
\fC1\fP   |   Missing required argument or unknown option
